leads.lead_text: Leaves white or greyish on lower surface, nutmeg-scented when crushed; anthers dehiscing by valves opening upward from base; fruiting receptacle dry, enclosing several silky, awned achenes
Leaves green on both surfaces, not or only weakly aromatic; anthers dehiscing by longitudinal slits; fruit an aggregate of small, fleshy, yellowish drupes
